tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE wrestling_feedback_ratings (
    event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_name VARCHAR(255),
    event_date DATE,
    match_type VARCHAR(50),
    fan_name VARCHAR(100),
    fan_email VARCHAR(255),
    feedback TEXT,
    rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE feedback_ratings (
  rating_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  event_id INT,
  match_id INT,
  rating INT,
  feedback TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Matches (
 match_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 event_id INT,
 match_type VARCHAR(50),
 winner VARCHAR(100),
 FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES WrestlingEvents(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Feedback (
 feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 match_id INT,
 rating INT,
 comments TEXT,
 FOREIGN KEY (match_id) REFERENCES Matches(match_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Matches (
    match_id INT,
    event_id INT,
    match_type VARCHAR(50),
    match_venue VARCHAR(50),
    match_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Feedback (
    feedback_id INT,
    match_id INT,
    fan_id INT,
    feedback_text VARCHAR(255),
    rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE MatchFeedback (
    match_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_id INT,
    feedback_text TEXT,
    rating INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES EventFeedback(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Match (
    match_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_id INT,
    wrestler1_id INT,
    wrestler2_id INT,
    winner_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES EventFeedback(event_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (wrestler1_id) REFERENCES Wrestler(wrestler_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (wrestler2_id) REFERENCES Wrestler(wrestler_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (winner_id) REFERENCES Wrestler(wrestler_id)
);
